channel.title: Tech
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from Tech, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: The US imposes 25% tariff on Nvidia’s H200 AI chips headed to China
item.description: The Trump administration formalized its 25% cut of H200 chip sales in China with a tariff that applies to certain semiconductors.

item.title: Taiwan to invest $250B in US semiconductor manufacturing
item.description: The U.S. struck a trade deal with Taiwan as the country looks to help boost domestic semiconductor manufacturing.

item.title: Best Packing Cubes for Every Kind of Trip (2026), Tested and Reviewed
item.description: Whether you’re a no-frills backpacker or a bag-checking fashionista, there’s a perfect packing cube out there for you.

item.title: How one startup is using probiotics to try and ease the copper shortage
item.description: Transition Metal Solutions is applying a special cocktail to coax microbes into unlocking more copper from ore.

item.title: Iran’s internet shutdown is now one of its longest ever, as protests continue
item.description: Iran’s government-imposed internet shutdown enters its second week as authorities continue their violent crackdown on protesters.

item.title: Wikimedia Foundation announces new AI partnerships with Amazon, Meta, Microsoft, Perplexity and others
item.description: The AI partnerships allow companies to access the org's content, like Wikipedia, at scale.

item.title: Spotify raises its subscription prices in the U.S. again
item.description: Spotify's new price for its individual plan is $12.99 per month

item.title: AI video startup, Higgsfield, founded by ex-Snap exec, lands $1.3B valuation
